.TH SHOAL-KERNEL 1 "July 2026" "Shoal 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
shoal-kernel \- run the resident Shoal execution kernel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shoal-kernel
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Serves authenticated Shoal sessions over a private Unix socket or inherited embedded descriptor.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-session " NAME"
Select a named session.
.TP
.BI \-\-socket " PATH"
Listen on PATH.
.TP
.BI \-\-state-dir " PATH"
Store durable state below PATH.
.TP
.BI \-\-token-store " PATH"
Use PATH as the credential authority file; overrides SHOAL_TOKEN_STORE.
.TP
.BI \-\-policy " FILE"
Load a sandbox policy.
.TP
.BR \-h , " \-\-help"
Print all limit and transport options.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shoal (1)
